column10:
[h1]Spoiler free review, with a short and a longer version:[/h1]

[h1]Short version:[/h1]


Buy this game if:

✅ You're into metroidvania alike games, HEAVILY FOCUSED ON FARMING resources;
✅ You can withstand a long,hefty text-based storytelling;
✅ topics such as: mental issues, family and other adult oriented subjects are up your alley;
✅ you're ready to invest at least 20 hours into the main game;

Don't buy if:

❌ the above points don't apply to you;
❌ repeated and unoptimized grinding aren't bearable to you (there's indeed a high chance that they won't);
❌ you were looking just for a swift and aesthetically pleasing and light hearted game;
❌ you've had or you're gonna grieve for the loss of someone you love and/or you were close to;


Verdict: 6,5 (a really stretched one) [b]WITH STRONG CAVEATS, please see below[/b]

Time required to finish the main game: 20/ 25 hrs (advice: keep a guide with you,even when not going for game achievements)
Time required to complete it at 100%: 33-35 hours (strongly advising to play with a collectible/missable items' guide)

[h1]Longer version:[/h1]

[b]1- what is this game? what's the core gameplay?[/b]

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2995812784

This is...a beautifully looking game, no doubt; [u]Charon (the former spiritfarer / psychopomp ) now needs a well deserved retirement. Now's your turn to take these "lost" souls into the Void/Everdoor/Last Step.
What will you do for at least 20 hours is to drive an upgradable ship between seas, storms and islands in order to gather souls, hoarding resources and completing (too) many errands for your guests and acquaintances, while trying to keep
them happy and well fed.[/u]

[b]2- Grind. Grind and more grind...however this is not Stardew Valley. Many quality of life changes could have been implemented easily:[/b]

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2995812936

Hoarding resources and travelling back and forth between locations is the core gameplay...and needs to be done...countless, countless times; sadly some aspects of travelling,hoarding and forging aren't opmimized, few important examples:

a) you can't delegate any minor task to anyone, all must be carried by your hands directly, even after fully upgrading your working stations;

b) there isn't a quick menù to keep track of your items' collection progress, while there's a handy one for building and upgrading structures;

c) the mission tracker doesn't have an option to quickly prompt you to a specifical location on the map, meaning that you'll have to manually search and pick it most of the time;

d) you can't quick travel once you enter your ship, either you take a bus which will take your ship into a nearby fast travel station or you'll have to enter the driver's cabin and reopen a menù;

You get my drift here...there's A WHOLE LOT OF CLICKING AND MENUS, even into the dialogues, which sometimes are way too long winded.
Luckly some characters really do shine in terms of animation and personality, if you've got yourself invested into the story, there's a high chance you won't forget this game.


Thanks for reading and for bearing up with me, leave a comment below if you have any questions or observations, have an amazing day/night, feel free to follow my other reviews at: https://store.steampowered.com/curator/32344423/

